Title: Loading code

Main Behavior:

1. User enters command to load code (e.g., 10 LOAD).
2. Computer spends the time to interpret the specified block as source text.
3. After loading completes, the user can observe the data stack contents on the stack status line.

Exceptional Behavior:

2a. If block does not exist, an error is displayed, and returns to the OK prompt.
2b. If a word named in the block does not exist, an error is displayed indicating the current block number and offset, and further interpretation of the block is aborted.

